{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place mint leaves in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place beetroot in mixing bowl and grate <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add vinegar, apple juice, pectin, sugar and salt. Replace measuring cup with simmering basket then bring to a rolling boil <nobr>45-60 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr> until setting point is reached (see tip). If mixture boils up onto lid, increase to speed 2, and decrease temperature to 95°C.  When liquid has settled, return to original settings and repeat as necessary.","Stir in reserved chopped mint using spatula. Transfer to a sterilised jar then seal and leave to cool. Serve cold; works well with roast lamb or pork."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["20 g fresh mint leaves","250 g beetroot, cooked, peeled, cut in pieces","125 g cider vinegar","300 g apple juice, unsweetened","100 g liquid pectin","125 g granulated sugar","½ tsp fine sea salt"]}],"id":"r94621","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-19ZIJ6_OFEQ\/XZadgz5vrKI\/AAAAAAAAgco\/aMAjs8eB14sD_8W2IVbwfFJe1wZVOl77QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_DOZi4RjIQteBVnAa.png","title":"Beetroot and Mint Jelly","publishedAt":"2015-12-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5.4 g","fat":"0.8 g","uom":"per 1 total recipe","carbohydrates":"184 g","calories":"3201 kJ \/ 765 kcal"},"usefulItems":"sterilised jam jar","hintsAndTricks":["Setting point test: place a saucer in the freezer for 5-10 minutes. Place 1 tsp jelly onto the saucer. After 30 seconds, push jelly with your finger. If it wrinkles, it is ready. If not, boil for a further <strong>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/strong>, then test again.","Can be made ahead then stored in the fridge until required.","This vibrant, sweet, soft-set jelly makes an excellent change from the various chutneys and sauces around. The mint gives it that distinctive English, summery flavour, while the earthy beetroot provides a glorious colour. It’s lovely with roast meats, cold meats and in sandwiches."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","1h","1 total recipe"]}